Both outputs are written and `transcript.json` validates against `transcript_schema.json`.

Across 25 iterations (74 hypotheses, 78 analyses) the dataset showed strong **prognostic** signals (ECOG, stage IV, albumin, weight loss, KRAS, BRAF V600E, right-sided primary, CEA, LDH, and — counter to the usual direction — older age associated with longer PFS) but **null treatment-and-biomarker-matching** effects: cetuximab × KRAS/NRAS/BRAF/right-sided, pembrolizumab × MSI-high, encorafenib × BRAF V600E, and trastuzumab/tucatinib × HER2 interactions were all non-significant despite adequate subgroup sample sizes. Regorafenib was the only treatment with a significant PFS difference (+0.97 mo, p<1e-216, in the opposite direction from the original later-line hypothesis). MSI-high, sex, race/ethnicity, insurance, comorbidity burden, symptom grades, and the 27-SNP panel all failed to associate with PFS.

